positions.title: Software Development Engineer Intern
positions.summary:
Developed features for a noSQL database GUI application such as: being able to import JSON templates from other AWS services and supporting bulk importing of data. These features aimed to solve customer problems on
an individual and enterprise level for integrating the application into existing workflow.


• Was able to solve challenges such as learning Vue and Typescript while on the job, and able to propose and create
everything from UI mockups, technical specifications, and implementation details to teammates and manager.


• Technology: Figma, Vue, Typescript, Electron, Jest, Webpack, Babel, Figma, Adobe XD

positions.title: Full-Stack Software Engineer and Manager
positions.summary:
Developed a full-stack POC and MVP product as the sole developer, which involved: creating a React dashboard
to manage and interface with group-therapy phone call sessions, writing a backend to integrate with a mySQL
database to store user profiles, and setting up a CI/CD pipeline with Heroku.


• When moving the product from MVP to a production level environment, I trained and managed other engineers to
help maintain and write code for user stories and coordinated with the CEO, UX team, remote developers, and advisors.


• Technology: React, Redux, Express, PostgreSQL, Zang (REST API Service), and Heroku.

positions.title: iOS Software Engineer Intern
positions.summary:
Developed a customizable UI module, for Chase iOS apps, that could adapt and offer different features depending
on the parameters and JSON responses that gets passed to it. The goal was to create different feature sets to help
increase customer engagement by 3 to 5 times and to standardize UI.


• Unit tested and implemented user stories in a SCRUM environment, and worked to sync with another Android
team to keep consistency in design.


• Technology: Swift, Xcode, Figma
